About Mahabalipuram

About Mahabalipuram

Chennai is among the fastest growing cities in the world, according to Forbes magazine. Home to around 7 million people, the Chennai International Airport, located in south-west Meenambakkam area, is at a distance of 19 km from the main city. Situated on the Bay of Bengal coast, Chennai has a network of national highways including the East Coast Road to its south, which can take you to the heritage town of Mahabalipuram, located in the Kanchipuram district of Tamil Nadu. Drive down to Mahabalipuram in your own car or alternatively, car for hire in Chennai . The Chennai to Mahabalipuram taxi fare can be quite expensive, so the best option is self-drive rental cars which are available from Zoomcar.

Chennai to Mahabalipuram by car

The best way to travel from Chennai to Mahabalipuram is by road with a distance of only 58 km that can be covered in an hour and a half. The connecting road from Chennai to Mahabalipuram is the scenic East Coast Road (ECR). Zoomcar can enable your trip by providing a self-drive Chennai to Mahabalipuram Cab of your choice at an affordable rate. Sign up on our website or mobile app and decide on the rental duration, pickup location, and car type. Zoomcar vehicles have an all-India permit and include fuel charges, damage insurance, roadside assistance, and all taxes in the rent.

Tourist places in Mahabalipuram

Famous for its 7th century Shore Temple that is located on the Bay of Bengal shore, Mahabalipuram (or Mamallapuram) is located to the south of Chennai. Places to visit in Mahabalipuram are the Pancha Rathas inspired by the Pandavas and Arjuna?s Penance. This UNESCO heritage site consists of many temples and rock carvings that were built during the reign of the Narsimha Varman dynasty. Other popular sites around Mahabalipuram that you can cover in your Zoomcar include the Tiger Cave and Tirukkalikundram with the hilltop Shiva temple. If you have more vacation time and are in the mood to travel, you can travel from Chennai to Pondicherry or Chennai to Kanchipuram using Zoomcar?s self-drive cars.
